      <pb n="1" facs="../images/26837_1.png" />
      <div>
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <placeName>Burlington N. Jersey</placeName>
            <date when="1853-06-27"><unclear>6mo.</unclear> 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>, 1853</date>
          </dateline>
        </opener>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p rendition="#indent">
          I take pleasure in introducing to your kind<lb />
          notice the bearer <persName ref="psn:peter_still">Peter Still</persName> who having by his<lb />
          industry purchased his own freedom is now<lb />
          endeavoring to purchase that of <persName ref="psn:vina_still">his wife</persName> &amp; children. He<lb />
          has as you will perceive by his papers received much<lb />
          encouragement &amp; "<hi rendition="#u">material aid</hi>" from the Benevolent<lb />
          upon whom he has called. Trusting he will<lb />
          continue to meet the same from those on whom<lb />
          he may call I leave him to the blessing of Providence<lb />
          and your sympathy and am <unclear>rs</unclear><lb />
        </p>

        <closer>
          <signed><persName ref="psn:dillwyn_smith">Dillwyn Smith</persName></signed>
        </closer>

        <pb n="2" facs="../images/26837_2.png" />

        <postscript>
          <ab>
            <add hand="#Unknown">
              Dillwyn Smith<lb />
              June 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> '53
            </add>
          </ab>
        </postscript>
      </div>
